post_text:
Our Mid Western League Organizers for the First Tech Robotics Challenge in Junction City are looking for volunteers for our upcoming meet on January 26th in Junction City. If you are interested in volunteering in Junction City at the meet let me know and I will pass it on to our coordinator.

Here is the help they are looking for:
ANYONE VOLUNTEERS: I am still in need of some volunteer positions, and these can be filled by parents/grandparents/brothers/sisters etc...

Field Resetters (2-4) they work noon-5pm
Judge Room Assistants (3) they will work 8am-noon
Volunteer Hospitality Room Helper (I need 2 adults to help keep the coffee brewing and the room organized throughout the day)
Pit Runners (2-4) they will work noon-3:30
Queuers (2) they will work noon-5

SPECIALTY VOLUNTEERS: These volunteers cannot be tied to a team as a mentor or parent and require some training. However, we CANNOT HAVE a tournament without them!

Judges (5) long day they work 8am-5pm **no robot knowledge needed, just needs to like kids***
Dean's List Judge (2) they will work 8am-11am

FIRST LEGO League INTO ORBIT 2018-2019 teaser

Heather Harrison‎Oakridge Robotics
August 31, 2018 at 1:14 PM ·

This year we are going to compete in the ORTOP First Lego League Challenge called Into Orbit! In order to prepare for the competitions there will be an after school club for two teams to design and build our Lego EV3 robots!!!

We need enough motivated students to fill two teams grades 4-8 and are always looking for adult volunteers to help out after school and at the exciting events. No experience necessary, just a willingness to helpout and have fun! Also, grade 8 students can participate in both FLL and First Tech challenges.

So far we have received an ODE grant to help out with some of the costs to start!!!

This year we are going to compete in the Robotics First Tech Challenge called Rover Ruckus! In order to prepare for the competitions there will be an after school club for two teams to design and build our competative robots!!! We now have a CNC router table, 100W lasercutter/engraver, 3D printers and a vinyl cutter to helpout with the build process of their amazing robots.
We need enough motivated students to fill two teams and are always looking for adult volunteers to help out after school and at the exciting events. No experience necessary, just a willingness to helpout and have fun!
https://youtu.be/A_e5r1lXraY
So far we have received a "Rookie" grant to help out with some of the costs to start!!!
https://youtu.be/XImFyFRmhRs

post_text:
A grant application was just submitted for two teams to compete next year in the Robotics First Tech Challenege and Robotics FIRST League for next school year! This should be a wonderful opportunity for students to learn news skills in construction, programming and troubleshooting while meeting and competing with other students from around the state. This year's competition theme is the Mars Rover called "Rover Ruckus." https://www.firstinspires.org/robotics/ftc

Here is last year's challenege: https://youtu.be/FHdfj1DH6Ys

Wish us luck with the application and competition!

post_text:
Today was the last day of classes. Thank you all for all of your support and kind words. This has been a great year of STEM hands-on projects and I look forward to next year!
We have some exciting additions to the Robotics class next year including a large cnc router, laser cutter and the First Tech Challenge to build a an autonomous vehicle to compete in the Mars Rover challenge! Thanks Heather Harrison for the help securing all of the grants to make this happen!!!

post_text:
A big thank you to the Eugene Masonic Lodge for their very generous donation last night to the Oakridge Robotics Class!!! Thank you for your initiative to help support rural robotics around Lane County!!! It will help to reach so many students. 😀

Recepients of the funds:
Oakridge Robotics
Pleasant Hill Robotics
Crow-Applegate Robotics
Lowell Robotics
